{"source_key":"sha256-c8597aca71664a84bdd657ea13dadbd3","record_index":1290,"record_hash":"sha256:caf4feab7aa7373e2efeefb79cc6b32beaab57d3392bee41bc7e52fb9aee58db","timestamp":"2026-05-20T02:30:25.150Z","kind":"tool_call","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:custom_tool_call","role":null,"text":null,"tool_name":"apply_patch","tool_input":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Update File: /Users/kiril/Documents/tars/Tars/02 [REDACTED:entropy].md\n@@\n-This note explores an evolution of `but-agentlog`: add a durable concept of an\n-agent session turn between the project-scoped session and the captured transcript\n-records.\n+This note explores an evolution of `but-agentlog`: add a durable concept of a\n+capture turn between the project-scoped session and the captured transcript\n+records.\n@@\n to immediately claim that the session \"belongs\" to a branch, commit, change, or\n pull request.\n+\n+## V1 Contract\n+\n+Implement v1 around persisted capture observations, derived indexes, and\n+read-time association. Do not persist inferred ownership.\n+\n+Persisted hierarchy:\n+\n+```text\n+project\n+  session\n+    capture turns\n+      transcript records\n+```\n+\n+Storage shape:\n+\n+```text\n+gitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:turns = list<TurnSummary JSON>\n+gitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:turn:<turn-key> = TurnDetail JSON\n+```\n+\n+Core rules:\n+\n+- A capture turn is created only when capture accepts at least one new\n+  transcript record.\n+- `TurnDetail.records` is an ordered array and is authoritative for rendering\n+  order within the capture turn.\n+- Backfilled capture turns may contain many logical conversation/provider turns,\n+  so records must carry provider/display grouping metadata when available.\n+- `turn_key` is `sha256-<32 lowercase hex chars>`, computed from UTF-8 stored\n+  `session_key`, `source_key`, and ordered record hashes separated by NUL bytes.\n+- Capture writes session/source metadata, transcript records, record hashes,\n+  turn summary, turn detail, and index entries in one logical GitMeta\n+  `apply_edits` batch.\n+- `previous_turn_key` points to the latest committed capture turn in the same\n+  session immediately before this turn.\n+- Environment snapshot collection is best-effort. Failed or partial snapshots\n+  may be enriched later on the same turn; do not create transcriptless turns.\n+\n+Environment and indexes:\n+\n+- Snapshot uncommitted worktree paths, stacks, branches, review identifiers,\n+  commits, change ids, and path-only commit file lists.\n+- Use an unpruned GitButler workspace/head-info API behind an agentlog-local\n+  adapter. Plain Git mode should come through the same shared path.\n+- Keep path lists capped at 256 entries. Keep commit lists capped per branch.\n+- Store `observed_targets` as a deterministic projection of the environment\n+  snapshot for branch, review, and change verification.\n+- Write only branch, review, and change indexes in v1. Do not write path or\n+  commit indexes.\n+- Hash branch, review, and change target key material for GitMeta index keys.\n+  Store index values as compact JSON strings containing `session_key` and\n+  `turn_key`.\n+\n+Read API shape:\n+\n+- `listSessions(project, filters, cursor)`\n+- `getSessionTimeline(session_key, window?)`\n+- `findRelatedSessions(target)`\n+- `getRelatedSessionDetail(target, session_key, turn_window, redaction_policy)`\n+- `previewReviewShare(target)`\n+\n+Product behavior:\n+\n+- Handoff reads a session timeline and can render records grouped by capture\n+  turn or logical conversation/provider turn.\n+- Review sharing starts from branch, review/PR, or change candidates, verifies\n+  hits against `TurnDetail.observed_targets`, then scores related sessions at\n+  read time.\n+- Automatic association is private discovery. Anything exposed outside normal\n+  repository-private scope must go through an explicit projection/redaction\n+  step.\n+- Results should be phrased as related-session evidence, not proof of authorship.\n+\n+V1 non-goals:\n+\n+- no durable inferred branch/PR/change ownership links\n+- no path index\n+- no commit index\n+- no separate checked-out refs field\n+- no graph `is_entrypoint` storage\n+- no commit message summaries in turn snapshots\n+- no index deletion/rebuild command\n+\n+The rest of this document explains the rationale and implementation details\n+behind that contract.\n \n ## Product Use Cases\n*** End Patch\n","source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T02:30:25.150Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","status":"completed","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]","name":"apply_patch"}}}